f:X \to \mathbb R
f(x)=\frac{d(a,x)}{d(a,b)}
(X,d)
a,b
X
d:X\times X\to \mathbb R
d(a,-):X\to \mathbb R
d(a,b)\ne 0
d(x,y)<d(a,b)\cdot\varepsilon
d(a,x)+d(x,y)\ge d(a,y)
d(a,y)+d(y,x)\ge d(a,x)
 |f(x)-f(y)| = \left|\frac{d(a,x)}{d(a,b)} - \frac{d(a,y)}{d(a,b)}\right| \le \frac{d(x,y)}{d(a,b)}<\varepsilon. 
\varepsilon>0
\delta =d(a,b)\cdot\varepsilon
